### =========================================================
### AEM EDS Admin API — wknd-backlink-test-sharepoint-external
### =========================================================
### Use with VS Code "REST Client" extension or IntelliJ HTTP client
### Preview = .aem.page (draft) | Live = .aem.live (production)
### Content source: SharePoint (external)
### =========================================================
###
### SETUP STEPS (one-time):
###
###   1. Create a GitHub repo with AEM EDS boilerplate code
###      - fstab.yaml should point to your SharePoint folder:
###        mountpoints:
###          /: https://adobeenterprisesupportaem.sharepoint.com/sites/eds-mmchome-test/Shared%20Documents/wkd-test-folder
###
###   2. Install AEM Code Sync on the repo
###      - Go to: https://github.com/apps/aem-code-sync/installations/new
###      - Select your account, add the repo, click Install
###
###   3. Share your SharePoint folder with helix@adobe.com (editor)
###      - In SharePoint, go to your site → Shared Documents → wkd-test-folder
###      - Click Share → enter helix@adobe.com → grant Edit access
###
###   4. Make sure your SharePoint folder has content
###      - At minimum: index (Word doc), nav, footer
###      - For redirects: an Excel workbook named redirects
###
###   5. Run the /code endpoint below to sync your repo config
###
###   6. Run the /preview endpoint to fetch content from SharePoint
###
###   7. Check /status — sourceLocation should show onedrive:
###
###   8. Open the preview URL in your browser to verify:
###      https://master--wknd-backlink-test-sharepoint-external--mimchome.aem.page/
###
### =========================================================

@base = https://admin.hlx.page
@org = mimchome
@repo = wknd-backlink-test-sharepoint-external
@branch = master
@site = {{org}}/{{repo}}/{{branch}}


### =========================================================
### CODE UPDATE (POST — forces EDS to re-read fstab.yaml)
### =========================================================
### Run this after changing fstab.yaml or any repo config.

### Refresh code/config
POST {{base}}/code/{{site}}/


### =========================================================
### PREVIEW (POST → .aem.page)
### =========================================================

### Preview home
POST {{base}}/preview/{{site}}/

### Preview trips
POST {{base}}/preview/{{site}}/trips

### Preview nav
POST {{base}}/preview/{{site}}/nav

### Preview footer
POST {{base}}/preview/{{site}}/footer

### Preview redirects sheet (.json suffix for Excel workbooks)
POST {{base}}/preview/{{site}}/redirects.json


### =========================================================
### PUBLISH (POST → .aem.live)
### =========================================================

### Publish home
POST {{base}}/live/{{site}}/

### Publish trips
POST {{base}}/live/{{site}}/trips

### Publish nav
POST {{base}}/live/{{site}}/nav

### Publish footer
POST {{base}}/live/{{site}}/footer

### Publish redirects sheet
POST {{base}}/live/{{site}}/redirects.json


### =========================================================
### STATUS (GET)
### =========================================================

### Status home
GET {{base}}/status/{{site}}/

### Status trips
GET {{base}}/status/{{site}}/trips

### Status redirects
GET {{base}}/status/{{site}}/redirects.json


### =========================================================
### UNPUBLISH (DELETE — clears CDN cache)
### =========================================================

### Unpublish adventures from live
DELETE {{base}}/live/{{site}}/adventures

### Unpublish adventures from preview
DELETE {{base}}/preview/{{site}}/adventures


### =========================================================
### PREVIEW URL (open in browser to verify)
### =========================================================
###
### https://master--wknd-backlink-test-sharepoint-external--mimchome.aem.page/


### =========================================================
### MICROSOFT GRAPH API — Manage redirects in SharePoint Excel
### =========================================================
###
### SETUP (one-time):
###   1. Go to https://portal.azure.com → Azure Active Directory
###   2. App registrations → New registration
###   3. Enable "Microsoft Graph" API permissions:
###      - Files.ReadWrite, Sites.ReadWrite.All
###   4. Create a client secret under Certificates & secrets
###   5. Copy Application (client) ID, Tenant ID, and Client Secret below
###
### GET YOUR ITEM PATH:
###   Your redirects workbook is at:
###   /sites/eds-mmchome-test/Shared Documents/wkd-test-folder/redirects.xlsx
###
### ALTERNATIVE: Use the SharePoint Online UI or Microsoft Graph Explorer
###   https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/graph-explorer

@graphBase = https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0
@tenantId = PASTE_YOUR_TENANT_ID_HERE
@graphClientId = PASTE_YOUR_CLIENT_ID_HERE
@graphClientSecret = PASTE_YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET_HERE
@graphToken = PASTE_YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@siteHost = adobeenterprisesupportaem.sharepoint.com
@sitePath = /sites/eds-mmchome-test
@driveItemPath = /wkd-test-folder/redirects.xlsx


### ---- STEP 1: Get access token (client credentials flow) ----
# @name getGraphToken
POST https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenantId}}/oauth2/v2.0/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{graphClientId}}&client_secret={{graphClientSecret}}&scope=https://graph.microsoft.com/.default&grant_type=client_credentials

### ---- STEP 2: Look up the SharePoint site ID ----
GET {{graphBase}}/sites/{{siteHost}}:{{sitePath}}
Authorization: Bearer {{graphToken}}

### ---- STEP 3: List drive items (find your redirects workbook) ----
GET {{graphBase}}/sites/{{siteHost}}:{{sitePath}}:/drive/root:/wkd-test-folder:/children
Authorization: Bearer {{graphToken}}

### ---- STEP 4: Read redirects from Excel workbook ----
### Reads used range from Sheet1
GET {{graphBase}}/sites/{{siteHost}}:{{sitePath}}:/drive/root:{{driveItemPath}}:/workbook/worksheets/Sheet1/usedRange
Authorization: Bearer {{graphToken}}

### ---- STEP 5: Append a redirect row ----
### Adds a row after the last used row in the table
POST {{graphBase}}/sites/{{siteHost}}:{{sitePath}}:/drive/root:{{driveItemPath}}:/workbook/worksheets/Sheet1/tables/1/rows/add
Authorization: Bearer {{graphToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"values": [["/old-path", "/new-path"]]}

### ---- STEP 6: Update a specific cell range (e.g. row 2) ----
PATCH {{graphBase}}/sites/{{siteHost}}:{{sitePath}}:/drive/root:{{driveItemPath}}:/workbook/worksheets/Sheet1/range(address='A2:B2')
Authorization: Bearer {{graphToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"values": [["/magazine", "/faqs"]]}
